    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >VRHandsFrame is a epoch-making VR overlay application that allows you to crop and analyze your VR view with intuitive hand gestures.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >While playing a VR game, users can use intuitive gestures to crop the scenery they see on the head-mounted display.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >You can also temporarily bookmark the cropped image in VR, or translate the text in the image.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" > Various actions on the cropped images</h2><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > Temporary saving in VR (bookmark)</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > Text translation</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > 2D code reading</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > Share images with Steam friends who owns VRHandsFrame</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >VRHandsFrame is like a secret tool that gives your VR life a Slightly-Futuristic experience.</p>",
